						               													<description>An n-in-a-row game with a twist for the Shibumi Game System.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board starts empty. Two players take turns handing a ball to their opponent to place, either on any empty board space or on any 2x2 platform. A player may not hand their opponent a ball of the color just placed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Example: Player 1 hands a Red ball to Player 2, who places it on the board. Player 2 may then hand a Black or White ball to Player 1, who places it on the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A player wins by making a full Black or White line, orthogonally or diagonally, on any level, on their turn.   A Red piece counts as both Black and White.  The winning line must contain at least one not-Red ball.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A full line on the 4x4 (board) level must be of length 4, on the 3x3 level must be of length 3, and on the 2x2 level must be of length 2.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Included in the Shibumi Rule Book&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Soft cover:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;http://www.lulu.com/shop/cameron-browne-and-nestor-romeral-andres/shibumi-rule-book/paperback/product-18940123.html&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Downloadable PDF:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;http://www.nestorgames.com/rulebooks/SHIBUMI_EN.pdf&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
